         <component>
            <section ID="i4i_dosage_admin_id_6eab6a3b-875a-47df-95df-1bf3bd6f0542">
               <id root="23ede28d-8f1a-40d2-a8de-df582c6d084a"/>
               <code codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" code="34068-7" displayName="DOSAGE &amp; ADMINISTRATION SECTION"/>
               <title>DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>The topical corticosteroids are generally applied to the affected area as a thin film from two to four times daily depending on the severity of the condition.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Occlusive dressings may be used for the management of psoriasis or recalcitrant conditions.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>If an infection develops, the use of occlusive dressings should be discontinued and appropriate antimicrobial therapy instituted.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20110120"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
